Important School Announcements - Spring Semester

Dear Parents and Guardians,

We hope this message finds you well. As the spring semester gets into full swing, we have several important updates regarding upcoming events and activities. Please read carefully and take note of any actions required.

1. Parent-Teacher Conferences: Parent-teacher conferences will be held on **March 15th and March 16th**. Slots are available from 3:00 PM to 7:00 PM on both days. You must sign up for a 15-minute slot by March 1st using the online portal (link will be sent separately by email on February 20th). Please ensure you have your child's student ID ready when signing up. Teachers will be available for all grades K-8.

2. Field Trip to Science Museum: The 5th Grade class will be going on a field trip to the City Science Museum on **April 5th**. A permission slip and payment of $25 per student are required by March 20th. Parents wishing to chaperone must undergo a background check. Contact Ms. Davis at ext. 203 for chaperone details. Packed lunch is required.

3. School Carnival Volunteers: We are still in need of volunteers for our annual School Carnival on **May 10th**. Various roles are available, including booth supervision, setup, and cleanup. All volunteers must register by April 15th through the school website. Specific shift assignments will be communicated one week prior to the event. A volunteer meeting might be held, but the date is TBD.

4. Summer Camp Enrollment: Information regarding our Summer Camp programs will be distributed during the first week of April. Early bird registration discounts will apply for sign-ups before May 1st.

Thank you for your continued support.
Sincerely,
Principal Thompson
`,
  ingestionTimestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
};

